<recipe>
<title>
White Pizza Dip Recipe
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 small boule
1 1/2 c . ricotta cheese part-skim ok
2 c . shredded mozzarella cheese
1/2 tsp . dried basil
1/2 tsp . dried oregano
Red pepper flakes
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Preheat oven to 350 F.
In a small bowl, stir together ricotta cheese and 1 1/2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese.
Stir in dried basil and oregano.
Cut top off inch or so off of boule.
Hollow out inside, leaving about a 1-inch or so rim.
Add mozzarella mixture to hollow.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup mozzarella cheese and red pepper flakes, to taste.
Grease a sheet of aluminum foil and lightly cover.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes covered.
Remove foil, and continue baking for 10-15 uncovered, or until hot and bubbly and cheese is melted.
</instructions>
</recipe>
